<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1436,1493,1999]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,313,1893,1919]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Remarks.</emphasis>
Linnaeus gave the 
<typeStatus box="[548,598,1893,1919]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">type</typeStatus>
locality of this species as ‘India’ (
<bibRefCitation author="Rockel, D. &amp; Korn, W. &amp; Kohn, A. J." box="[1013,1237,1893,1919]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" pagination="84" refId="ref46330" refString="Rockel, D., Korn, W. &amp; Kohn, A. J. (1995) Manual of the living Conidae. Vol. 1: Indo-Pacific. Christa Hemmen Verlag, Wiesbaden, pp. 516, pl. 84." type="book chapter" year="1995">
Röckel 
<emphasis box="[1107,1168,1893,1918]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">et al.</emphasis>
1995
</bibRefCitation>
) without precise locality data. This record appears to be first to give the exact locality of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[1038,1137,1933,1958]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="miles">
<emphasis box="[1038,1137,1933,1958]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">C. miles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1180,1244,1933,1959]" name="India" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">India</collectingCountry>
. This species is extremely rare along the 
<collectingRegion box="[443,574,1973,1999]" country="India" name="Tamil Nadu" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">TamilNadu</collectingRegion>
Coast.
</paragraph>
